ItacAcademyItem.Notes:
Motto from Virgil, Aeneid, VI.
For a short account of the Agghiacciati Academy see Giammaria Mazzucchelli, Gli Scrittori D`Italia, Brescia, 1753, Vol. I; Raffaele Starrabba, Dell`Accademia Palermitana detta degli Agghiacciati, Archivio Storico Siciliano, IV, 1879;
According to Vincenzo Castelli (Fasti di Sicilia, Messina, 1820), the Agghiacciati Academy was founded under the auspices of Viceroy Pedro Téllez-Girón, III Duke of Ossuna. This may date its foundation to 1616 and 1620.
